THE MAN FROM U.N.C.L.E. 
Stars: Robert Vaughn (Napoleon Solo), David McCallum (Illya Kuryakin), Leo G. Carroll (Alexander Waverly)

401. The Summit-Five Affair    9/11/1967  
Visiting Berlin headquarters in preparation for a high level U.N.C.L.E. conference, "Summit Five," Solo finds agent Heinz Newman (Don Chastin) mysteriously murdered. Illya goes to Berlin, as does Harry Beldon (Albert Dekker), one of Waverly&#039;s counterparts in Section 1. Beldon suspects that either Solo or Gerald Struthers (Lloyd Bochner) committed the murder, while Illya suspects Beldon&#039;s secretary Helga Deniken (Suzanne Cramer), but Beldon himself turns out to be the traitor, and he plans to kill Waverly at the conference.

Writer: Robert E. Thompson
Director: Sutton Roley
Guest star: Albert Dekker (Harry Beldon), Lloyd Bochner (Gerald Strothers), Susan Cramer (Helga Deniken), Don Chastain (Arthur Newman), James Millhollin ("Wraith-like"), Barbara Moore (Lisa Rogers)
